## Description

I have added a notebook for figure 11.18 which was screenshot previously. I have considered following points in notebook: 

1. Current figure does not show the target distribution from where these samples are taken. I have also checked the references ([paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/1903.08008) & [book](http://www.stat.columbia.edu/~gelman/book/) - Fig 11.3 by Dr. Vehtari) given in caption, but they also didn't mention target distribution. Hence I took bimodal normal distribution as shown in the first subplot.
2. In the book2, section-11.6.2.2, Dr. Kevin mentioned that "_Although the above definition can detect non-convergence of the kind shown in Figure 11.18(a), it will fail on non-stationary chains of the kind shown in Figure 11.18(b)._" But in the current figure, we can not visually see if **old $\hat{R}$** is failing in the 2nd subplot or not (since the author didn't show the numbers). So I have calculated this old $\hat{R}$ for both situations.  
which would help to understand the insight- "we are getting $\hat{R}=1.003$ despite the chain is not converged yet."  

Dr. @murphyk, please review the above changes. 
## Question
1. I am confused about how to mention R_hat (which is calculated as per the old definition) in the title? does the current version look good or do we need like - old $\hat{R} = 1.003$ 
- One alternative could be, keep this version and mention in caption clearly that  $\hat{R}$ is calculated as per old definition using equation x.y

## Description

Changes:
1. Converted `funnel_numpyro.ipynb` to blackjax
2. I have merged the **old code** for 11.20(a) & 11.20(b, c) into a single notebook - `funnel_numpyro.ipynb`. we are keeping this for comparison purposes.
3. I have merged the **updated code** for 11.20(a) & 11.20(b, c) into a single notebook - `neals_funnel.ipynb`. So we need to change caption as well. 

## Potential problems/Important remarks
I have the following confusion in related section 11.6.4:
1. In Eq. 11.123 & 11.126, I think we should replace `v` to `v/2` (Image1 & Image2). I have written code considering `v/2`. ([reference](https://num.pyro.ai/en/latest/examples/funnel.html))
**Image1:**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/59387624/174488816-0a0a2aab-a0d1-471b-8ec5-ac9724057efd.png)

**Image2:**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/59387624/174488825-d4d04940-e65b-49d8-a3b7-a3bd53cfb355.png)

2. The term `variance v` looks confusing to me (Image3), because if we are doing $exp(v/2)$ then shouldn't $v$ looks like log (variance)?

**Image3:**
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/59387624/174488937-23fde5ec-e86a-4abf-a509-ad7831afb2b9.png)

pr_title: Added example of change of variable in HMC
pr_body:
This PR is adding an example notebook for the change of variable in HMC as discussed in #252. This notebook mainly demonstrates,
1. BlackJAX implementation of Binomial hierarchical model
2. Change of variable trick in `logprob()` using jacobian  
3. Using `arviz` plots to analyze MCMC diagnostics. 

Let me know if I have to update anything in the notebook.

**Note:** [Original source](https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/blob/507eb851e7156abf8a5bba66c1ff03f36c3e42c9/notebooks/book2/03/hierarchical_binom_rats.ipynb) of this notebook is Dr. Kevin's pyprobml repo.

pr_title: fixed import errors by wrapping try...except
pr_body:
## Description

I have fixed 17 notebooks that were failing due to missing packages, I wrapped them by try...except manually. 

Some notebooks were directly downloading helper scripts from pyprobml repo using `wget` commands. I moved these scripts to pyprobml-utils so we can use these scripts by importing them. I have created following PRs in the `probml-utils` for the same.

1. [Added mnist_helper_tf.py](https://github.com/probml/probml-utils/pull/2)
2. [ Added lvm_plots_utils.py, vae_conv_mnist.py](https://github.com/probml/probml-utils/pull/3)

This PR will enable to run 2nd workflow (static_import_check) successfully and unblock 3rd workflow (execute_notebooks) which depends on the completion of 1st workflow and 2nd workflow, both.


## Issue
#773

pr_body:
## Description This PR is regarding the updated-URL mapping of the book1's backward compatibility. I have done the following changes. 1. I detected dead URLs as mentioned in issue: #776 and fixed them by taking appropriate action as shown in table below. - I have added code to detect urls in `probml_utils.url_utils` in this [PR](https://github.com/probml/probml-utils/pull/4) | Fig | Notebook | Action | | -- | -- | -- | | 1.12 | emnist_viz_jax.ipynb | 1. emnist_viz_jax.ipynb moved from probml-notebooks/notebooks to pyprobml/notebooks/book1/01/
2. emnist_viz_pytorch.ipynb removed from pyprobml | | 9.6, 9.7 | naive_bayes_mnist_jax.ipynb | 1. naive_bayes_mnist_jax.ipynb moved from probml-notebooks/notebooks-d2l to pyprobml/notebooks/book1/09/
2. naive_bayes_mnist.ipynb removed from pyprobml| | 15.25 | positional_encoding_jax | 1. positional_encoding_jax.ipynb moved from probml-notebooks/notebooks-d2l to pyprobml/notebooks/book1/15/
2. positional_encoding.ipynb removed from pyprobml| | 19.14 | hbayes_maml.ipynb | moved from probml-notebooks/notebooks to pyprobml/notebooks/book1/19/ | |20.24, 20.25, 20.26 | ae_mnist_conv.ipynb | moved from probml-notebooks/notebooks to pyprobml/notebooks/book1/20 | Still, 3 notebooks would be fixed by @patel-zeel by changing the name of the notebook in the latex source code. - 3.13: Rename to mix_bernoulli_em_mnist.ipynb - 4.17: Rename to gauss_infer_2d.ipynb - 9.5: Rename to fisher_discrim_vowe.ipynb 2. I have created 25 dummy notebooks (mentioned in this issue: #777 ) for figures which has more than one notebook, this dummy notebook has a caption associated with that figure and pointers to corresponding notebooks. 3. Then I created a mapping between fig_no and actual_url to pyprobml repo. This mapping will be used to update links in firestore database. - [misc/mapping_figures_to_urls.ipynb](https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/compare/master...karm-patel:dead_urls?expand=1#diff-63b03a1b9bad644fa5d6d328099a193dc49fcfb782ae8437659411f39873ffa4) contains code to reproduce step-2 and step-3. 4. Updated .gitignore to add .lof file. **NOTE**: Dr. @murphyk, currently 2nd workflow (static_import_check) is failing, because d2l-notebooks is moved to pyprobml repo and imports in that repo is not wrapped with try...except. soon it will be fixed.

pr_body:
## Description

- Added a table containing `fig_name` & `fig_height`. ([fig_height_book1.md](https://github.com/karm-patel/pyprobml/blob/fig_height_mapping/internal/fig_height/fig_height_book1.md), [fig_height_book2.md](https://github.com/karm-patel/pyprobml/blob/fig_height_mapping/internal/fig_height/fig_height_book2.md)).
- This mapping would be useful for contributors while doing latexifying tasks. They can give the exact height (in `latexify()`) of the figure given in latex source code, so there are fewer chances of compressing the image (e.g. 3in figure to 1.5in)
- However `TexSoup` is not able to read 48 `.tex` files from total of 607 tex files. I kept a list of these files in `internal/fig_height/tex_defective.txt` Later we can handle these files using pure regex scrapping. 

I'll link these `.md` file to dashboard #739 once this PR gets merged.
<!-- Please refer to https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md and/or https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/blob/master/notebooks/README.md before opening this PR -->

## Issue
Task 8 of #862

pr_body:
## Description
Extension of PR #896 
1. Some `.tex` files were not able to be parsed by `TexSoup`, now these files are handled by the regex
2. `book1.lof` & `book2.lof` updated
3. Merged `internal/fig_height/fig_height_book1.md` & `internal/fig_height/fig_height_book2.md` to `internal/fig_height/fig_height_mapping.md`

## Remarks
As you suggested, I've tried to add `fig_no` to this table, but could not get success, due to the following reasons.
1. .lof contains `notbook_name` & `fig_no`
2. .latex contains `notebook_name` & `fig_name`
3. But since many notebooks create multiple figures and also some figures are generated by multiple notebooks (in the case of subplots), hence I am not able to exact mapping between `fig_no` and `fig_name` for most of the figures.   

But I think to just know `fig_height` (for latexify task), `fig_name` is enough and one can easily use ctrl+F.

## Description

- Added [common_readme.md](https://github.com/karm-patel/pyprobml/blob/common_readme/internal/common_readme.md) which contains notebook_name, colab link and github link

I am enlisting advantages of having this file just for recap:
1. Now we don't need firestore redirection, so adding a new notebook would be easy. 
2. We don't need duplicate notebooks in separate folders which point to the root notebook.
   - Currently, we can remove book2 duplicate notebooks, but not book1 to maintain backward compatibility.
3. We don't need dummy notebooks like `fig_10_9.ipynb` anymore.
   - Again we can remove `fig_x_y.ipynb` from book2, but not book1

- There were some notebooks with identical content or either of them latexified and other is not. I've updated all such notebooks such that we will have only a single root notebook and other notebooks would have pointers to this root notebook.

pr_body:
## Description
closes #1054
Note that this change will reflected in printed version of book1 not the draft of book1.
1. Previously `code.probml.ai/book1/` was pointing to an individual notebook colab link, but since we have updated our redirection flow using `notebooks.md`, these URLs should be pointed to this common .md file.
2. I have updated firestore with these updated URLs, some of the examples are below
https://code.probml.ai/book1/2.3
https://code.probml.ai/book1/8.17
3. Removed duplicate notebooks in book1
4. **Note:** We still need dummy notebooks "fig_8_26.ipynb"
 <!-- Please refer to https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md and/or https://github.com/probml/pyprobml/blob/master/notebooks/README.md before opening this PR -->
